      "writtenOn": "2021-04-28T21:50:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You can get rid of \u0027newpath\u0027 since in the end it is just \u0027temp\u0027 with \u0027/\u0027 prepended if necessary. AFAICT, temp will normally begin with \u0027/\u0027, and it appears Rockbox interprets a path like \u0027foo/bar\u0027 as \u0027/foo/bar\u0027 anyway. I\u0027m not 100% certain of the existing logic, but I doubt prepending \u0027/\u0027 directly to temp will cause problems.",
      "revId": "74a3cd8ff926259922f6a83c63cc4e1ac8780f4e",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
