    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0b840535_c279bdf6",
        "filename": "apps/menus/playlist_menu.c",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000721
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T01:16:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In my testing, having a path that lacked \u0027/\u0027 completely, like just \u0027foo\u0027, caused an issue in playlist_start() for some reason. Or, at least that\u0027s where the simulator appears to segfault. I can try to prepend \u0027/\u0027 directly to temp though.",
      "parentUuid": "9337f95f_c00f85ec",
      "revId": "74a3cd8ff926259922f6a83c63cc4e1ac8780f4e",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16e0c690_95e7ed55",
        "filename": "apps/menus/playlist_menu.c",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000718
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-28T21:50:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "strncpy is not in Rockbox\u0027s libc so this doesn\u0027t link on native targets. Just use strcpy here. temp appears to be null terminated by construction, if not then it\u0027s a bug in other functions.\n\nAlso, if strlen(temp) \u003d\u003d MAX_PATH then newpath will not be null terminated.\n\nBut see my comment above about getting rid of newpath, which would make these issues moot.",
      "revId": "74a3cd8ff926259922f6a83c63cc4e1ac8780f4e",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "246f95af_50a60d8b",
        "filename": "apps/menus/playlist_menu.c",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000721
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T01:16:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e strncpy is not in Rockbox\u0027s libc so this doesn\u0027t link on native targets. Just use strcpy here. temp appears to be null terminated by construction, if not then it\u0027s a bug in other functions.\n\nWill be fixed in next patchset\n\n\u003e Also, if strlen(temp) \u003d\u003d MAX_PATH then newpath will not be null terminated.\n\u003e \n\u003e But see my comment above about getting rid of newpath, which would make these issues moot.\n\nBased on my testing of rockbox crashing when no \u0027/\u0027 is present in the path at playlist_start() for some reason, perhaps then temp should be sized to MAX_PATH + 2? \n\nThough the only time that would be a concern is if someone used a filename that was the maximum path length, without a \u0027/\u0027, in the root directory. I\u0027m not even sure if the original function checked for that condition when appending \".m3u8\" to the filename. All the same, should probably protect against that scenario.",
      "parentUuid": "16e0c690_95e7ed55",
      "revId": "74a3cd8ff926259922f6a83c63cc4e1ac8780f4e",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
