    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9521a7f8_75515c51",
        "filename": "apps/menus/playlist_menu.c",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 132,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000718
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-28T21:50:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t like this hack. Worse, the logic breaks down if you enter the current playlist menu by pressing the WPS hotkey because it gets to the playlist viewer by another means. (hotkey is not on all players, btw.)\n\nRockbox already keeps track of the current activity in a stack, but you can only query the current activity and I don\u0027t think that\u0027s enough for what you need to detect.\n\nI *think* you\u0027d want to check if the activity stack looks like this--\n\n(bottom of stack) \u003e ... \u003e ACTIVITY_WPS \u003e ... \u003e ACTIVITY_PLAYLISTVIEWER (top of stack)\n\nie. we were in WPS activity and after that got to the playlist viewer somehow. See apps/misc.c, get_current_activity(). It should be easy to add another function which checks for nested activities like above and then use it instead of this variable hack.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 132,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 132,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "74a3cd8ff926259922f6a83c63cc4e1ac8780f4e",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8181e2ce_2dea58f4",
        "filename": "apps/menus/playlist_menu.c",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 132,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000721
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T01:16:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I don\u0027t like this hack.\n\nMe neither. But, it was the only way I could think of to get this information into here without modifying each function to pass it as a parameter to get from there to here. I think it\u0027s 4 or 5 function calls.\n\nI actually wasn\u0027t aware there was an activity stack, I\u0027ll try to figure out how it works. If it\u0027s \"last in first out\" (I think), then I could just search for ACTIVITY_WPS at a specified spot to see if that\u0027s where we came from. It might get messy though if the user wanders around the context menu in and out of stuff before landing in the save playlist screen.",
      "parentUuid": "9521a7f8_75515c51",
